definitions.definition: An abbreviation formed by the initial letters of other words.

subdefinitions.definition: Generally such abbreviations, including those pronounced as individual letters ( initialisms such as " TNT ").
Exclusively such abbreviations when pronounced as a word (as " laser " or " NATO ").

definitions.definition: An abbreviation formed by the beginning letters or syllables of other words (as " Benelux ").

main_definition: ( linguistics ) An abbreviation formed by the initial letters of other words.
secondary_definitions: ( linguistics ) An abbreviation formed by the beginning letters or syllables of other words (as " Benelux ").
